# CHILD SAFETY REVIEW PROTOCOL

Run this checklist BEFORE Libby tests the app for the first time, and again before
any public release. This is non-negotiable.

---

## CONTENT SAFETY

- [ ] No child's real name is hardcoded anywhere in the UI (must come from store, not code)
- [ ] All visible text passes TinyStories-1500 vocabulary review
- [ ] All hint text has been reviewed — no confusing, scary, or inappropriate language
- [ ] All lore messages are warm, encouraging, and age-appropriate
- [ ] No developer debug text is visible to the child (__DEV__ gates confirmed)
- [ ] No placeholder text ("Lorem ipsum", "TODO", "test string") in any visible UI

---

## PARENT CONTROL SAFETY

- [ ] All parent-only actions require the PIN — child has no bypass path
- [ ] Graduation gate requires minimum mastery requirements AND parent PIN
- [ ] Daily time limit (3-hour hard cap) is implemented and enforced
- [ ] Parent manual completion confirmation requires a deliberate tap (no misclick risk)
- [ ] "Guardian" label used consistently for parent in all in-app text

---

## DATA SAFETY

- [ ] No child name, age, or grade is sent to any external server except Star Mail
- [ ] Camera (motion verify) processes on-device only — zero data transmitted
- [ ] No third-party analytics, ad networks, or tracking SDKs are present
- [ ] .env Supabase keys are real and the database has Row Level Security active
- [ ] Star Mail only stores parent-authored messages — no child behavioral data

---

## TECHNICAL SAFETY

- [ ] App runs fully offline (core features) — test with airplane mode enabled
- [ ] Skia components all have useEffect cleanup for SkImage/SkPicture
- [ ] No crashes on Fire HD 10 during a normal 15-minute session
- [ ] largeHeap: true confirmed in app.json
- [ ] App recovers gracefully from being backgrounded and reopened

---

## PRE-PUBLIC LAUNCH ADDITIONS (Phase 4)

These are NOT required for Libby's private September test, but required before App Store:
- [ ] COPPA verifiable parental consent flow at onboarding
- [ ] Privacy policy live at a real URL
- [ ] CA SB 243 AI watermark visible on all AI-generated content screens
- [ ] Data deletion mechanism available to parents
- [ ] App Store children's category compliance confirmed
